# SoftwareMetrics charter

## Goal

Multi-language **static and hybrid** analysis: Kotlin, TypeScript + React, Rust.

## Metrics (product scope)

- Cyclomatic complexity; coupling (fan-in/fan-out over internal imports); cohesion (average LCOM); duplication; composition vs inheritance ratio.
- Naming conventions (language-idiomatic); SRP heuristics; method/class length.
- **LLM-assisted** comment and documentation quality only when explicitly enabled (deterministic metrics stay reproducible without a model).

## Engineering defaults

- Shared **metric/reporting model**; per-language **analyzers** behind a narrow interface.
- Prefer AST-based, testable logic; document thresholds and rule IDs for each metric.
